ctually, looking at the original PoC crash: \"WRITE of size 49 at 0x502000000020\". The buffer is 16 bytes, address 0x502000000020 is exactly 16 bytes from start (0x502000000010 + 16 = 0x502000000020). So writing 49 bytes starting at buffer would write from offset 0 to offset 48, which goes from 0x502000000010 to 0x502000000040. But the overflow is detected at 0x502000000020 (the first byte after the buffer).\n\nFor variant_4 with \"short\" (6 bytes including newline or 5+null), it shouldn't overflow. Unless... let me check if maybe the input has no null terminator? Or maybe strcpy keeps reading past intended length?\n\nActually, I think I need to understand what \"WRITE of size 23\" means. It could be that ASan intercepts strcpy and reports the size of the write operation it detects. Or maybe there's something about how the variants are being passed.\n\nLet me create a simple test to understand the boundary:", "refusal": null, "role": "assistant", "annotations": null, "audio": null, "function_call": null, "tool_calls": [{"id": "call_00_8IgQ87xuyQWc6FfZJv3b3WxF", "function": {"arguments": "{\"command\": \"cd /src && for len in 15 16 17 20 30; do echo \\\"Testing string of length $len:\\\"; python3 -c \\\"print('A'*$len, end='')\\\" | ./vuln \\\"$(cat)\\\" 2>&1 | grep -E \\\"PROBE|ERROR|Successfully\\\" | head -5; echo \\\"---\\\"; done\"}", "name": "bash"}, "type": "function", "index": 0}]}}], "created": 1774407915, "model": "deepseek-chat", "object": "chat.completion", "service_tier": null, "system_fingerprint": "fp_eaab8d114b_prod0820_fp8_kvcache_new_kvcache", "usage": {"completion_tokens": 653, "prompt_tokens": 12418, "total_tokens": 13071, "completion_tokens_details": null, "prompt_tokens_details": {"audio_tokens": null, "cached_tokens": 12288}, "prompt_cache_hit_tokens": 12288, "prompt_cache_miss_tokens": 130}}, "prompt_tokens": 12418, "completion_tokens": 653, "agent_id": null}
